      <title>1835 Jan. 5, Peyton's Creek, Smith County [Tennessee to unknown recipient] / [Adam Fergusson]</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This is a letter dated January 5, 1835 to an unknown person. It is probably from Adam Fergusson who is head of Tennessee's pension office. Fergusson asks the recipient some questions about pension law, especially pertaining to widows and heirs of deceased soldiers. He also enquires about a recently passed Congressional act.</abstract>
